---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Getting Started with Tour Scout',
  description: 'Learn how to get started with Tour Scout, your AI-powered tour planning assistant.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Getting Started with Tour Scout</h1>
    
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">1. Sign Up</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Create your Tour Scout account to access all features. Click the "Sign Up Now" button on the home page
          or <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/5kA03B9He1Ll1EcaLn" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">sign up here</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">2. How to Log In to Tour Scout</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Use the same email you signed up with to access the GPT here: 
          <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-67e60e8bfa2481918f948a7e28905145-scout-the-tour-assistant" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">Scout GPT</a>
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">
          Important: Your login is case-sensitive — make sure to type your email exactly as you did when signing up
        </p>
        <p class="text-base mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          If you're not seeing full access after logging in, try refreshing the window and entering your email again.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">3. Join Our WhatsApp Beta Crew</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          This is where we drop quick tips, feature updates, sneak peeks, and let you vote on what Scout learns next.
          <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdwB7YieTUfmI1L5mhyrjtVBFJQbtb0CrOq2JRK9aEP0Wa1FA/viewform" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">
            Join the WhatsApp Crew
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">4. Start Strong — Quick Use Cases</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Here's what beta users say they love using Scout for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li><strong>Show Day Rundown:</strong> Nearby food, errands, late night eats, wellness, driver hotels, etc.</li>
          <li><strong>Routing Help:</strong> Multi-city planning with stopover recs and drive times</li>
          <li><strong>Day Off Ideas:</strong> Chill spots, crew-friendly bars, walkable hotels, etc.</li>
          <li><strong>Production Vibes:</strong> Load-in logistics, errand runs, airport times</li>
          <li><strong>Mental Health Wins:</strong> Calm parks, sleep tips, and crew-first design</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2 italic text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">→ Just drop in your dates and cities. Scout does the rest.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">5. Pro Tip: Ask Scout Anything</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Scout isn't just a location tool. It's a thinking partner. Have conversations with it about:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>Your tour struggles</li>
          <li>Managing mental health on the road</li>
          <li>Navigating career growth and transitions</li>
          <li>Learning tour skills or strategies you didn't even know you needed</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Whether you're solving a real problem or just thinking out loud — Scout's built to listen, adapt, and help. 
          Scout's trained on real tour knowledge, not generic search results.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">6. Having Trouble Logging In?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Here's what to try if you're having issues accessing Scout — it's usually a quick fix:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>Double-check that you're using the same email you used to purchase access — it's case-sensitive, so type it in exactly as you did when signing up</li>
          <li>Try refreshing the page and re-entering your email when prompted</li>
          <li>Still stuck? Reach out to us directly at <a href="mailto:concertindustryhelp@gmail.com" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">concertindustryhelp@gmail.com</a> and we'll get you sorted fast</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">7. Payment & Account Help</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Our payment system is handled by Auth Flow.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>For any questions regarding your billing account, email <a href="mailto:support@authflow.ai" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">support@authflow.ai</a></li>
          <li>To cancel or manage your subscription, go to the original confirmation email from Auth Flow — it includes your personalized link to manage billing</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">8. Can I Share My Account?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          No, your Tour Scout account cannot be shared. Each account is specifically tied to your email address and includes a unique authentication token that's linked to your IP address and device. This security measure ensures:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>Your personal tour data and preferences remain private</li>
          <li>Our AI can provide personalized recommendations based on your specific needs</li>
          <li>We can maintain the quality of service for all users</li>
          <li>Your account security is protected from unauthorized access</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          If you need access for multiple team members, please contact us at <a href="mailto:concertindustryhelp@gmail.com" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">concertindustryhelp@gmail.com</a> to discuss team account options.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">9. You're helping shape the future of touring.</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Thanks for jumping into the beta. See you in the chat. See you on the road. Let's make this smarter.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Interested in collaborating with us? We'd love to hear from you! Reach out to us at 
          <a href="mailto:concertindustryhelp@gmail.com" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">concertindustryhelp@gmail.com</a> 
          to discuss how we can work together to improve the touring experience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <a href="/" class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 font-medium">&larr; Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout> 